dcterms:creator: R. Godahewa
C. Bergmeir
G. I. Webb
R. J. Hyndman
P. Montero-Manso
dcterms:description: The Nasa Turbofan dataset contains 4 datasets where engines operate under different conditions, providing distributional shifts between each other. It is used for predicting the remaining useful life of turbofan engines by using sensor information extracted from them.
dcterms:title: Nasa Turbofan

dcterms:creator: D. Dua
C. Graff
dcterms:description: The Beijing Air Quality dataset contains hourly meteorological measurements from 12 stations between 2013 and 2017, used to predict the concentration of PM10 in the air.
dcterms:title: Beijing Air Quality

dcterms:creator: D. Dua
C. Graff
dcterms:description: The Bike Sharing dataset collects hourly meteorological data combined with the number of bikes rented by a bike sharing company, used to predict bike rental amounts.
dcterms:title: Bike Sharing

dcterms:creator: D. Dua
C. Graff
dcterms:description: The PMS dataset is part of the Beijing Air Quality dataset, specifically focusing on the first year of measurements (2013) used as source data for predicting PM10 concentrations.
dcterms:title: PMS (Beijing Air Quality)

dcterms:creator: D. Dua
C. Graff
dcterms:description: The PMT dataset is part of the Beijing Air Quality dataset, focusing on the early months of the last year (2016-2017) used as target training data for predicting PM10 concentrations.
dcterms:title: PMT (Beijing Air Quality)

dcterms:creator: D. Dua
C. Graff
dcterms:description: The BKS dataset is part of the Bike Sharing dataset, focusing on data from fall, winter, and spring used as source data for predicting bike rentals.
dcterms:title: BKS (Bike Sharing)

dcterms:creator: D. Dua
C. Graff
dcterms:description: The BKT dataset is part of the Bike Sharing dataset, focusing on data from summer used as target data for predicting bike rentals.
dcterms:title: BKT (Bike Sharing)
